1. Moj *život* je pun izazova. (My life is full of challenges.)
2. *Životi* životinja su ugroženi zbog ljudske aktivnosti. (The lives of animals are endangered due to human activities.)
3. Ovaj film prikazuje *život* jedne porodice tokom 20. veka. (This movie depicts the life of one family during the 20th century.)
4. Oni *životi* su bili ugroženi zbog prirodne katastrofe. (Their lives were endangered due to a natural disaster.)
5. Šta misliš o smislu *života*? (What do you think about the meaning of life?)
6. Njihovi *životi* su se promenili nakon što su dobili na lutriji. (Their lives changed after winning the lottery.)
7. Ona voli da putuje i upoznaje nove *živote*. (She loves to travel and meet new lives.)
8. Sve je počelo kao običan dan, a završilo se kao najgori dan u mom *životu*. (It all started as a regular day and ended up being the worst day of my life.)
9. Njena strast su knjige o *životima* poznatih ljudi. (Her passion is books about the lives of famous people.)
10. Naši *životi* su puni izbora, ali to takođe znači i da moramo preuzeti odgovornost za svoje odluke. (Our lives are full of choices, but that also means we have to take responsibility for our decisions.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "životi" can be either a plural form of "život" (life), or a third-person singular present tense of the verb "živeti" (to live). The translations of the sentences reflect the different meanings accordingly.